index 0000000..9439ca4
--- /dev/null
+++ b/_docs/frame-integration.md
@@ -0,0 +1,59 @@
+# Frame portfolio integration
+
+The portfolio links to Frame as an independent application. It does not proxy,
+embed, authenticate, poll, or fetch Frame during startup or request handling.
+Frame outages therefore cannot delay portfolio pages, search, shop, or checkout.
+
+## Configuration
+
+`FRAME_ORIGIN` is the only configuration input. When it is unset, links use
+`https://frame.engmanager.xyz/`. HTTPS preview origins and HTTP loopback
+origins such as `http://127.0.0.1:3100/` are valid overrides. Credentials,
+non-root paths, query strings, fragments, non-loopback HTTP, and malformed
+values fail startup validation.
+
+The initial integration is deliberately static. No `frame-client` dependency,
+background poller, status snapshot, or status state is enabled. Consequently,
+the optional healthy/stale/not-configured presentation and its data TTL are
+not applicable to this stage. Enabling public data later requires a separate
+review against Frame's public contract, strict bounded background refresh, and
+tests proving that handlers remain I/O-free.
+
+## Search, cache, and browser boundaries
+
+- The homepage card and shared article/search navigation use the same validated
+  origin and ordinary top-level navigation.
+- The soft-navigation router declines cross-origin destinations, and the
+  service worker declines cross-origin requests. Neither fetches or caches a
+  Frame response.
+- Portfolio HTML remains public and contains only static copy and the public
+  Frame origin. No Frame status, identity, title, media URL, object key, or
+  response body enters HTML, logs, search, RUM, or cache tags.
+- The apex canonical, robots response, and sitemap remain apex-only. Frame owns
+  its canonical, robots, and sitemap policy.
+- The portfolio security headers remain unchanged. This stage adds no iframe,
+  CORS, cookie, camera, microphone, display-capture, or `postMessage` boundary.
+- A request carrying the production Frame host receives `421 Misdirected
+  Request` instead of portfolio or shop markup. Cloudflare and Render remain
+  the authoritative production host split.
+
+## Release and rollback record
+
+Source acceptance does not launch the link. Production exposure remains gated
+by the Frame subdomain launch runbook.
+
+Record each rollout without requiring an atomic cross-repository deploy:
+
+| Field | Value |
+| --- | --- |
+| Portfolio commit | `<engmanager.xyz SHA>` |
+| Frame UI commit | `<Frame Render SHA>` |
+| Frame API commit | `<Frame Worker SHA>` |
+| Frame contract major | `1` |
+| Preview evidence | `<portfolio preview + Frame preview URLs/run>` |
+| Production evidence | `<headers/cache/navigation run>` |
+
+Roll back the portfolio commit to remove the card and nav link. That rollback
+does not alter Frame DNS, Worker routes, Render, authentication, D1, R2, or
+media. If live public data is introduced later, disable it before removing the
+static link.
